messages.message:
i updated my local docker for desktop  and have started seeing this error when i try to build webapp image for local

``` => ERROR [builder 8/9] ADD build/generated-docs /home/ibuser/builddocs/content/reference/refiner/                                                                                                                                       0.0s
------
 > [builder 8/9] ADD build/generated-docs /home/ibuser/builddocs/content/reference/refiner/:
------
rpc error: code = Unknown desc =  not found: not found
make: *** [build-docker-minikube] Error 1```
Any suggestions?
Try the docker build with —no-cache
good suggestion, but no luck :disappointed: also tried `docker builder prune --filter "type=source.local"`
@will any other suggestion?
Do any of the other targets work?
Just vanilla make build-docker for example
`apps-server` image was built successfully. i think this has something to with docs.
Can you build-docker on the same service?

```Sending build context to Docker daemon  123.8MB
Step 1/12 : FROM ubuntu:18.04
 ---> 549b9b86cb8d
Step 2/12 : RUN apt-get update -y
 ---> Running in 6c11e9f9bd16
apt-get: error while loading shared libraries: /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libbz2.so.1.0: invalid ELF header
The command '/bin/sh -c apt-get update -y' returned a non-zero code: 127
make[1]: *** [build-docs-docker] Error 127
make: *** [fetch-docs] Error 2```
That... is weird
That’s not even the new docs, that’s from the autogenerated doc container
Though this is starting to make sense. If the refiner docs don’t generate, you can’t copy them
i did not expect make build-docker to work, because we skip `fetch-docs` for make-docker-minikube
Yeah we can’t skip fetch-docs :D
Actually
Yes
I can help
lets hop on a call?
We can touch the directory it needs
